<paragraph id="0854369FFF9FFFD7FE92FB1C5A39A7CE" blockId="1.[335,867,1245,1272]" box="[335,867,1245,1272]" pageId="1" pageNumber="434">
<heading id="531C81F3FF9FFFD7FE92FB1C5A39A7CE" bold="true" box="[335,867,1245,1272]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="434" reason="2">
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9FFFD7FE92FB1C5A39A7CE" bold="true" box="[335,867,1245,1272]" pageId="1" pageNumber="434">
Key to the Philippine species of 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D1CFF9FFFD7FD2EFB1F5A39A7CE" authorityName="Eschscholtz" authorityYear="1829" box="[755,867,1245,1272]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9FFFD7FD2EFB1F5A39A7CE" bold="true" box="[755,867,1245,1272]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="434">Anthaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="40F16514FF9FFFD4FFACFAD55D3DA722" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="435" pageId="1" pageNumber="434" type="key">
<keyStep id="B31F2E3AFF9FFFD7FFACFAD55D1AA6D9" pageId="1" pageNumber="434">
<paragraph id="0854369FFF9FFFD7FFACFAD55D1AA659" blockId="1.[113,1089,1303,1583]" pageId="1" pageNumber="434">
<keyLead id="B31A95AAFF9FFFD7FFACFAD55D1AA659" pageId="1" pageNumber="434">
1. Elytra parallel for anterior two thirds; elytral margins straight, or only slightly emarginate posteriad humeri; abdominal segments completely covered by elytra. .............................. ...................... subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D1CFF9FFFD7FE41FA945B91A659" authority="Eschscholtz, 1829" authorityName="Eschscholtz" authorityYear="1829" box="[412,715,1366,1391]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9FFFD7FE41FA945B58A659" bold="true" box="[412,514,1366,1391]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="434">Anthaxia</emphasis>
Eschscholtz, 1829
</taxonomicName>
(does not occur in the 
<collectingCountry id="70FC760FFF9FFFD7FC1DFA955D60A659" box="[960,1082,1367,1391]" name="Philippines" pageId="1" pageNumber="434">Philippines</collectingCountry>
)
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0854369FFF9FFFD7FFACFAB55D1AA6D9" blockId="1.[113,1089,1303,1583]" pageId="1" pageNumber="434">
<keyLead id="B31A95AAFF9FFFD7FFACFAB55D1AA6D9" pageId="1" pageNumber="434">
– Elytra more or less sphenoidal, tapering posteriorly; elytral margins distinctly, very often deeply emarginate posteriad humeri; lateral portions of abdominal segments usually not covered by elytra, well-visible in dorsal view (more distinct in males) (subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D1CFF9FFFD7FC38FA745833A6D9" authority="Reitter, 1911" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9FFFD7FC38FA74598CA6D9" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="434">Haplanthaxia</emphasis>
Reitter, 1911
</taxonomicName>
). ....................................................................................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="B31F2E3AFF9FFFD4FFACFA355D3CA205" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="435" pageId="1" pageNumber="434">
<paragraph id="0854369FFF9FFFD7FFACFA355D1AA519" blockId="1.[113,1089,1303,1583]" pageId="1" pageNumber="434">
<keyLead id="B31A95AAFF9FFFD7FFACFA355D1AA519" pageId="1" pageNumber="434">2. Elytral epipleura reaching only apical rounded part of elytra; head narrower than anterior pronotal margin; median lobe of aedeagus with lateral serration. ................................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0854369FFF9CFFD4FF4AFF1E5D3CA205" blockId="2.[151,1127,219,1044]" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">
<keyLead id="B31A95AAFF9CFFD4FF4AFF1E5D3CA205" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">– Elytral epipleura reaching middle of apical rounded part of elytra (but not reaching elytral suture); head wider than anterior pronotal margin; median lobe of aedeagus without lateral serration. .......................................................................................................................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="B31F2E3AFF9CFFD4FF4AFEFE5D3CA122" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">
<paragraph id="0854369FFF9CFFD4FF4AFEFE5D3DA282" blockId="2.[151,1127,219,1044]" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">
<keyLead id="B31A95AAFF9CFFD4FF4AFEFE5D3DA282" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">
3. Frons convex, microsculptured; lateral pronotal margins subparallel, maximum pronotal width at midlength; elytra subparallel at anterior two thirds; anal ventrite of female rounded apically; aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation id="90D02A1AFF9CFFD4FE64FEB95B5DA2A2" box="[441,519,379,404]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="7.[113,152,1427,1446]" captionTargetBox="[113,1086,219,1277]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[113,1088,219,1278]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs. 7–14. 7–9 – Habitus. 7 – Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) palawanensis sp. nov., holotype (♂, 3.6 mm, Palawan); 8 – A. (H.) philippinensis sp. nov., holotype (♂, 3.6 mm, Sibuyan); 9 – A. (H.) philippinensis sp. nov., allotype (♀, 3.9 mm, Luzon). 10–14 – Aedeagi (not in the scale). 10 – A. (H.) palawanensis sp. nov., holotype; 11 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis Fisher, 1922, Mindoro; 12 – A. (H.) philippinensis sp. nov., holotype; 13 – A. (H.) boettcheri Obenberger, 1928, Luzon, Abra province; 14 – A. (H.) attenuata Fisher, 1922, holotype, Negros." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5331373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5331373/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
; 
<quantity id="CF139B7AFF9CFFD4FDCFFEB95BCCA2A5" box="[530,662,379,403]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="435" unit="mm" value="3.75" valueMax="3.9" valueMin="3.6">
<figureCitation id="90D02A1AFF9CFFD4FDCFFEB95B38A2A5" box="[530,610,379,403]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[151,190,1282,1301]" captionTargetBox="[151,1126,221,1260]" captionTargetId="figure-11@6.[151,1126,219,1262]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Habitus. 1 – Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) attenuata Fisher, 1922, holotype (♂, 4.0 mm, Negros); 2 – A. (H.) boettcheri Obenberger, 1928, lectotype (♂, 5.0 mm, Luzon); 3 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis Fisher, 1922, holotype (♀, 3.5 mm, Mindanao); 4 – A. (H.) boettcheri (♂, 3.9 mm, Luzon, Abra province); 5 – A. (H.) boettcheri (♀, 4.7 mm, Luzon, Abra province); 6 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis (♂, 3.5 mm, Mindoro)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5331369" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5331369/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">3.6–3.9</figureCitation>
mm
</quantity>
; 
<figureCitation id="90D02A1AFF9CFFD4FD7CFEB95A5CA2A2" box="[673,774,379,404]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="7.[113,152,1427,1446]" captionTargetBox="[113,1086,219,1277]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[113,1088,219,1278]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs. 7–14. 7–9 – Habitus. 7 – Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) palawanensis sp. nov., holotype (♂, 3.6 mm, Palawan); 8 – A. (H.) philippinensis sp. nov., holotype (♂, 3.6 mm, Sibuyan); 9 – A. (H.) philippinensis sp. nov., allotype (♀, 3.9 mm, Luzon). 10–14 – Aedeagi (not in the scale). 10 – A. (H.) palawanensis sp. nov., holotype; 11 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis Fisher, 1922, Mindoro; 12 – A. (H.) philippinensis sp. nov., holotype; 13 – A. (H.) boettcheri Obenberger, 1928, Luzon, Abra province; 14 – A. (H.) attenuata Fisher, 1922, holotype, Negros." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5331373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5331373/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">Figs. 8, 9</figureCitation>
. Luzon, Negros, Sibuyan. .......... ........................................................................................... 
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9CFFD4FCC0FE595D3DA282" bold="true" box="[797,1127,411,436]" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D1CFF9CFFD4FCC0FE595D50A282" authority="Bílý &amp; Kubáň, 2012" authorityName="Bílý &amp; Kubáň" authorityYear="2012" box="[797,1034,411,436]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippinensis" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9CFFD4FCC0FE595A6FA285" bold="true" box="[797,821,411,435]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9CFFD4FC98FE5E5A3BA285" bold="true" box="[837,865,412,435]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9CFFD4FCADFE595D50A282" bold="true" box="[880,1034,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">philippinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="21AC57F6FF9CFFD4FBCCFE5E5D3DA282" box="[1041,1127,412,436]" pageId="2" pageNumber="435" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0854369FFF9CFFD4FF4AFE7E5D3CA122" blockId="2.[151,1127,219,1044]" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">
<keyLead id="B31A95AAFF9CFFD4FF4AFE7E5D3CA122" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">– Frons flat with feeble medial groove, without microsculpture; lateral pronotal margins rounded, maximum pronotal width at posterior third or at midlength; elytra tapering from humeri to apex; anal ventrite of female notched apically. ............................................... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="B31F2E3AFF9CFFD4FF4AFDDE5D3CA1C2" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">
<paragraph id="0854369FFF9CFFD4FF4AFDDE5D3CA142" blockId="2.[151,1127,219,1044]" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">
<keyLead id="B31A95AAFF9CFFD4FF4AFDDE5D3CA142" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">
4. Pronotum distinctly wider than elytra, maximum pronotal width at midlength; parameres with fine dorsal denticulation at posterior half, aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation id="90D02A1AFF9CFFD4FC82FDF95AF4A162" box="[863,942,571,596]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="7.[113,152,1427,1446]" captionTargetBox="[113,1086,219,1277]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[113,1088,219,1278]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs. 7–14. 7–9 – Habitus. 7 – Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) palawanensis sp. nov., holotype (♂, 3.6 mm, Palawan); 8 – A. (H.) philippinensis sp. nov., holotype (♂, 3.6 mm, Sibuyan); 9 – A. (H.) philippinensis sp. nov., allotype (♀, 3.9 mm, Luzon). 10–14 – Aedeagi (not in the scale). 10 – A. (H.) palawanensis sp. nov., holotype; 11 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis Fisher, 1922, Mindoro; 12 – A. (H.) philippinensis sp. nov., holotype; 13 – A. (H.) boettcheri Obenberger, 1928, Luzon, Abra province; 14 – A. (H.) attenuata Fisher, 1922, holotype, Negros." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5331373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5331373/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
; 4.0 mm; 
<figureCitation id="90D02A1AFF9CFFD4FBFDFDF95D3BA162" box="[1056,1121,571,596]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[151,190,1282,1301]" captionTargetBox="[151,1126,221,1260]" captionTargetId="figure-11@6.[151,1126,219,1262]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Habitus. 1 – Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) attenuata Fisher, 1922, holotype (♂, 4.0 mm, Negros); 2 – A. (H.) boettcheri Obenberger, 1928, lectotype (♂, 5.0 mm, Luzon); 3 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis Fisher, 1922, holotype (♀, 3.5 mm, Mindanao); 4 – A. (H.) boettcheri (♂, 3.9 mm, Luzon, Abra province); 5 – A. (H.) boettcheri (♀, 4.7 mm, Luzon, Abra province); 6 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis (♂, 3.5 mm, Mindoro)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5331369" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5331369/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
. Negros. ............................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="CFEB4D1CFF9CFFD4FCFCFD995D3CA142" authority="Fisher, 1922" authorityName="Fisher" authorityYear="1922" box="[801,1126,603,628]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="attenuata" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9CFFD4FCFCFD995A86A145" bold="true" box="[801,988,603,627]" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9CFFD4FCFCFD995A63A145" bold="true" box="[801,825,603,627]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9CFFD4FC94FD9E5A3EA145" bold="true" box="[841,868,604,627]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="3A9FEA8DFF9CFFD4FCA9FD9E5A86A145" bold="true" box="[884,988,604,627]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">attenuata</emphasis>
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6C7A4B6EFF9CFFD4FC3FFD995D3CA142" author="FISHER W. S." box="[994,1126,603,628]" pageId="2" pageNumber="435" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref5662" refString="FISHER W. S. 1922: New buprestid beetles from Borneo and the Philippines Islands. Proceedings of the United States National Museum No. 2428 61 (7): 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="1922">Fisher, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0854369FFF9CFFD4FF4AFDBE5D3CA1C2" blockId="2.[151,1127,219,1044]" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">
<keyLead id="B31A95AAFF9CFFD4FF4AFDBE5D3CA1C2" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">
– 
